<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2019] Writing on a disconnected socket on Mac causes SIG PIPE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2019</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Suppose you have a successful client / server connection on Mac.  The client suddenly disconnects while the server is writing the reply to the socket.  Currently, this causes SIG PIPE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thrift already has code to deal with this on Linux, but Mac / BSD do this differently.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac OSX&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
